# Repository Sanitization & Privacy Audit

Systematically identify and remove all personal data, sensitive configurations, and unnecessary development artifacts from the `zget` repository to ensure a safe and professional public release.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This plan involves rewriting major parts of the documentation to reflect the new "Museum Pro" / "Vault" branding and the retirement of the TUI.

## Proposed Changes

### [Documentation]

#### [MODIFY] [README.md](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/README.md)

- Update intro to emphasize **The Archivist**, **The Vault**, and **The Portal**.
- Add "Integrated Player" and "iOS/PWA Optimization" to the features list.
- Update quick start to focus on the PWA installation and server exposure.
- Add section on the "Integrity Repair" system.

#### [MODIFY] [AGENTS.md](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/AGENTS.md)

- Expand instructions for AI agents.
- Clarify the architectural triad (Archivist/Vault/Portal).
- Detail the handoff process between `zget` and other agents (e.g., Librarian).

#### [MODIFY] [project.md](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/openspec/project.md)

- Update tech stack to include PWA specificities (manifest, service workers).
- Refine design principles to include "Museum Quality Content" (H.264 prioritization).

#### [MODIFY] [AGENTS.md](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/openspec/AGENTS.md)

- **BIG REWRITE**: Remove all TUI references.
- Remove mention of `tui/app.py`.
- Update directory structure and component map to the headless server model.

#### [MODIFY] [README.md](file:///Users/base/Projects/bubroz/README.md)

- Update the `zget` description from "Archival TUI" to "The Archival Engine (The Archivist, The Vault, The Portal)".
- Highlight the 2026 high-fidelity PWA features.

### [Component Name]

#### [MODIFY] [.gitignore](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/.gitignore)
- Add explicit exclusions for `*.log`, `*.png` (unless in static), and any other temp artifacts.
- Ensure `libs/` and `scripts/` are fully ignored if intended for local use only.

#### [DELETE] [server.log](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/server.log)
#### [DELETE] [server_debug.log](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/server_debug.log)
- These contain local terminal paths and internal network IPs.

#### [DELETE] [__pycache__](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/) (Recursive)
- Remove all compiled Python files from the Git index.

#### [MODIFY] [Codebase Sanity Check]
- Search all [.py](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/cli.py), [.md](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/AGENTS.md), and [.html](file:///Users/base/Projects/story-time-animated-hero/index.html) files for literal strings like `192.168.`, `/Users/base`, or specific test URLs that might be personal.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification

- Review all modified `.md` files for consistency and clarity.
- Ensure no TUI or outdated path references remain.
- verify that the GitHub profile update accurately represents the project's current state.

### Automated Checks
- Run `git ls-files` and `git status` to ensure only essential files are tracked.
- Run `grep -r "192.168." .` and `grep -r "/Users/" .` to confirm no remaining leaks.
- verify that the GitHub profile update accurately represents the project's current state.
